ch to the sign problem,\nthat seems to offer much room for improvements. An appealing feature of this\napproach is its generality. It is illustrated first in the simple case of a\nscalar field theory with chemical potential, and then extended to the more\nchallenging case of QCD at finite baryonic density.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 May 2012 18:05:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 17 Jul 2012 05:53:57 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 27 Sep 2012 14:28:26 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 13 Jul 2015 02:54:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-14"}
